# Cursor Enforcement Layer

This file defines how architectural rules must be enforced during code generation.

---

# 1. Pre-Generation Validation

Before generating any code:

- identify module type (ui / feature / shared / infra)
- determine owning rule file
- validate dependency direction

If invalid → do not proceed

---

# 2. Dependency Safety Check

Never generate:

- cross-feature imports
- shared → feature imports
- UI → infra direct access
- feature → feature coupling

---

# 3. Layer Compliance Rule

All code must belong to a valid architectural layer:

- UI layer (ui-boundaries)
- Feature layer (feature-architecture)
- Shared layer (shared-layer)
- Infrastructure layer (boundaries)

No hybrid modules allowed.

---

# 4. Abstraction Control

Do not create shared abstractions unless:

- reused in at least 2 domains
- proven necessity exists

Prefer duplication over premature reuse.

---

# 5. System Guarantee

If respected:

- zero architectural violations at generation time
- predictable module placement
- enforced clean architecture without manual policing